    "stem": "An agent contacts an existing whole life policyowner every two years and convinces her to surrender her current policy's cash value and use it to purchase a new whole life policy from the same insurer. Each time, the policyowner incurs new sales charges and begins a new surrender charge period, while the agent earns a new first-year commission. This repeated pattern is BEST described as:",
