    "stem": "A policyowner conducts a Section 1035 tax-free exchange, transferring the cash value of an old life insurance policy into a new one. The old policy had an outstanding loan of $15,000, which the insurer forgives/extinguishes rather than carrying it over to the new policy. How does the IRS treat the extinguished $15,000 loan?",
